    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The Random Forest model significantly outperformed linear regression, achieving lower MAE and higher R² across both cross-validation and test evaluation. Feature importance analysis (without `avg_speed`) shows that task duration is primarily driven by interaction difficulty and environmental complexity, particularly collision count, path length, and obstacle density.\n",
        "\n",
        "Residual analysis indicates improved handling of complex scenarios, although prediction error remains higher in challenging environments such as S9_hard. The model is therefore selected for deployment in the capstone system, where it provides robust task duration estimates to support time-aware planning and adaptive decision-making."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jKhh5JnUGJ7_"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# 4. Task 2: Classification Modelling"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZA3PEq1-emAW"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The goal of this task is to predict `success`, enabling the assistant to estimate whether the mug-fetching task is likely to be completed successfully and to adapt policy decisions accordingly."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "TCM6XBYTl_4G"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 4.1 Feature Selection and Data Split"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "iK_tF5gLmUzy"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#Selected features\n",
        "features_cls = [\n",
        "    'path_len_m',\n",
        "    'obstacles_seen',\n",
        "    'grasp_attempts',\n",
        "    'doors_opened',\n",
        "    'avg_speed',\n",
        "    'collision_count',\n",
        "    'cupboard_open_init',\n",
        "    'clutter_level',\n",
        "    'distractors_level'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "X_cls = df[features_cls]\n",
        "y_cls = df['success']\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SC3sTAZveoZ-"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Train/test split\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train_cls, X_test_cls, y_train_cls, y_test_cls = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X_cls,\n",
        "    y_cls,\n",
        "    test_size=0.20,\n",
        "    random_state=42,\n",
        "    stratify=y_cls\n",
        ")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "B7WPOqp3ezTd"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 4.2 Shared Preprocessing Pipeline"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "g1_86CP-mf2k"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Standard scaler\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n",
        "\n",
        "preprocessor_cls = ColumnTransformer(\n",
        "    transformers=[\n",
        "        ('num', StandardScaler(), features_cls)\n",
        "    ]\n",
        ")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PMligwCJe2do"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 4.3 Model Comparison"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "APvdDfUhm5B6"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Pipeline initialisation\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
        "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_validate, KFold\n",
        "\n",
        "log_pipeline = Pipeline(steps=[\n",
        "    ('preprocessor', preprocessor_cls),\n",
        "    ('model', LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "cv = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "log_cv = cross_validate(\n",
        "    log_pipeline,\n",
        "    X_train_cls,\n",
        "    y_train_cls,\n",
        "    cv=cv,\n",
        "    scoring=('accuracy','precision','recall','f1','roc_auc')\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'Metric': log_cv.keys(),\n",
        "})\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
