      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "False negatives are more costly than false positives, as failing to identify high-risk scenarios may lead to collisions or unsafe behaviour. Therefore, the decision threshold is set to be more conservative, increasing sensitivity to lower predicted success probabilities and ensuring that risky conditions are more likely to be flagged.\n",
        "\n",
        "Overall, task duration is primarily influenced by movement efficiency (e.g. speed and path length), while task success is more strongly driven by interaction complexity and environmental difficulty."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CrFX-x1ben1k"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# 5. Task 3: Clustering, Association Rules, and Anomaly Detection"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DxQ6JVgwhUqD"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 5.1 Clustering"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Icz9eTOwlxze"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Selected features\n",
        "cluster_features = [\n",
        "    'path_len_m',\n",
        "    'obstacles_seen',\n",
        "    'grasp_attempts',\n",
        "    'doors_opened',\n",
        "    'avg_speed',\n",
        "    'collision_count',\n",
        "    'cupboard_open_init',\n",
        "    'clutter_level',\n",
        "    'distractors_level'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "X_cluster = df[cluster_features]\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cFdB-uc8hcAF"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Standard scaler\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_cluster)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HK6z4YMaiFbm"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Cluster Selection"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KTOCKh67oHH6"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# K- range, Silhouette & Davies Boulden\n",
        "# ------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import davies_bouldin_score\n",
        "\n",
        "sil_scores = []\n",
        "db_scores = []\n",
        "k_range = range(2, 9)\n",
        "\n",
        "for k in k_range:\n",
        "    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)\n",
        "    labels = kmeans.fit_predict(X_scaled)\n",
        "\n",
        "    sil_scores.append(silhouette_score(X_scaled, labels))\n",
        "    db_scores.append(davies_bouldin_score(X_scaled, labels))\n",
        "\n",
        "pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'k': list(k_range),\n",
        "    'Silhouette': sil_scores,\n",
        "    'Davies_Bouldin': db_scores\n",
        "})\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
